claim.claim-text:
1. A fuel cell vehicle comprising:
a vehicle body having a floor frame;
front wheels;
rear wheels;
a fuel cell that generates electricity by the electrochemical reaction of hydrogen and oxygen; and
a subframe on which the fuel cell is mounted, being attached to the lower side of the floor frame and has a pair of side frames that extend in the fore-aft direction of the vehicle body;
wherein the lower end of each side frame is formed to have a recess portion so that the portion located substantially midway between the front wheels and the rear wheels is the highest point from the tire-ground contact surface.
